<h1>Collection Help</h1>

<section class="dash-content-section">
	<h2>What is a Collection?</h2>
	<p>
	A collection is a group of objects that share the same schema. For example, a collection of blog posts.
	Each object in a collection is an instance of the schema that the collection is based on.
	</p>

	<h2>Setup Default Collections</h2>
	<p>
	If this is a new project, you can use the Project Setup tool to help you create some
	starter collections. Or add your own collections with the New Collections button at the
	bottom of this page.
	</p>
	<a class="dash-button transparent" href="utils/project-setup">Project Setup Tool</a>

	{% set inaccessibleCollections = cms.admin.inaccessibleCollections() %}
	{% if inaccessibleCollections|length > 0 %}
	<div class="edition-alert">
		<span class="icon-warn"></span>
		<div class="edition-alert-content">
			<strong>{{ inaccessibleCollections|length }} collection(s) unavailable</strong>
			<p>The following collections use schemas that require a higher edition:</p>
			<ul>
			{% for collection in inaccessibleCollections %}
				<li>{{ collection.label ?? collection.id }} <code>{{ collection.schema }}</code></li>
			{% endfor %}
			</ul>
			<a href="utils/license-manager" class="dash-button">Upgrade to Regain Access</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	{% endif %}
</section>
